olarising interventions by the central government and Laudian ecclesiastical authorities during Charles I’s Personal Rule. The second half of the book provides a rich and detailed analysis of petitioning movements and side-taking in Cheshire in 1641–2. An important contribution to understanding the local origins and outbreak of civil war in England, the book will be of interest to all students and scholars studying the English revolution.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGentryzEnglandzCheshirexHistoryy17th century. 0aGentryzEnglandzCheshirexHistory. 0aReligion and politicszEnglandzCheshirexHistoryy17th century. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / Stuart Era (1603-1714).2bisacsh  aCheshire.  aEnglish civil war.  aLaudianism.  aPersonal Rule.  aallegiance.  acounty community.  aculture wars.  amonarchical republic.  anews.  apetitioning.  apuritanism.1 aCust, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLake, Peter, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLake, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611442640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526114426423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526114426/original  a978-3-11-128248-0  Manchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packageb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles